Ok so I am working like 7 days a week with both jobs.  I haven't had a day off in a month and it's starting to get to me now.  I am tired all day long even when I sleep the other half of the day.  The only reason I get up is to go to work.  It's alright though.  I'm making money and it's not like I have that much else to do.  Except trying to date someone but thats not working because I am working all the time.  Knowing how this dating thing happened last time it won't work but I have to try.  I am working full time at Kroger and part time at Babies R Us.  I wish I had a set schedule.  The only thing that is set is that I have wednesdays and fridays off at Kroger to work at Babies R Us.  Making almost $11 an hour rocks though.  It's better then the $6.76 an hour I make at Babies R Us.  That just wasn't paying anything.  Now I am paying stuff off and still have some money left over.  Not that I have anything to show for it since I am not saving any of the money I earn.  Soon I might learn to save money.  I have Thanksgiving at my moms house but only after I worked that day thanks to Kroger.  That's alright though since I figured that I would have to work.  It was just me and my mom this year for the holidays so we didn't have to work all that turkey dinner stuff out around other family members.  Saturday the 19th I had Thanksgiving dinner with my roommates family.  I'm kinda still part of the family even though he is married and stuff.  Family by association now I guess is what I am.

So I've been working at Kroger again now.  This will be my third week back.  Everyone seems to like me there and I'm well known or something like that.  For the last 3 weeks I've been getting all the late shifts.  Mostly 5p.m. to 1 a.m., the earliest I've gotten off was midnight but even still was late enough.  The earliest I get off this week is 8p.m. I'm guessing that's to keep me at the 35 hours I'm only supposed to be getting or something.  It's all good though.  I'm making $10.95 an hour and the checks are weekly and a good amount.  I am still working part time at Babies R Us part time two days a week. Working there Wednesday's and Friday's with eight hour shifts.  So I get 16 hours a week there at $6.76 an hour.  Now you see why I went back to Kroger.  It's wierd though being at Kroger because I see all these familiar faces from when I worked at my home store that is down the street from the store I am working at now.  I've seen about 10-15 different people that were regulars at my old store.  Last night I even saw a co-manager that I worked with over at the Plano store.  I couldn't remember his name but he remembered mine.  Next week I think that they are going to start me working in Customer Service.  Ahh customer service... I had to work so hard to get out of there at the old store and I'm going to get stuck right back in there.  What else am I going to do though?  I need the money and I get enough right now so I can't really complain too much.

Are you tired of all those sissy friendship poems that
always sound good,
but never actually come close to reality? Well, here
is a series of promises that really speaks to true
friendship:

1. When you are sad -
I will help you get drunk and plot revenge against the
sorry bastard who made you sad.
2. When you are blue -
I will try to dislodge whatever is choking you.
3. When you smile -
I will know you finally got laid.
4. When you are scared -
I will rag on you about it every chance I get.
5. When you are worried -
I will tell you horrible stories about how much worse
it could be and to quit whining.
6. When you are confused -
I will use little words.
7. When you are sick -
Stay the hell away from me until you are well again. I
don't want whatever you have.
8. When you fall -
I 
will point and laugh at your clumsy ass.

This is my oath...I pledge it till the end. 
Why? You may ask.
Because you are my friend.
Send this to 10 of your closest friends, then get
depressed because you can only think of two and one of
them isn't speaking to you right now anyway.

Remember:
A good friend will help you move. A really good friend
will help you move a body.
Let me know if I ever need to bring a shovel.

I started at a new Babies "R" Us store today that's here in TX.  UUggghhh.  New people + new environment = uncomfortable Jade.  Well eventually I will get used to it but I want to be at my old store with my old co-workers. Well some of them at least lol.  Jessa you were right about Sharon.  I saw her the other day at her Kroger so I could talk to her about working at Kroger.  She does look a little older.  She is the same ole Sharon though.  I was thinking today on how I do kinda miss working for Kroger.  Although the whole time I worked there I was like I hate this place I want to work somewhere else.  The job I have now is so boring it's not even funny.  It doesn't get busy during the week and only gets a little busier during the week.  Jessa have they moved you guys to another store yet?  Where did you say they were moving you guys too?  I'm not even close to being able to work in the area that I'd like to.  I'm in Dallas but on the border of Mesquite and Garland area.  It sucks because nobody I know live out here.  I know I don't know a whole lot of people but still I'm not even close to the people I do know.  Gas is like $3.00 a gallon.  I put $11.00 of gas into my car last night and it wasn't even four gallons and it was only a little over 1/4 of a tank.  What a gip..  Oh well gotta get used to it I guess.  I guess it's a good thing work is not even 15 minutes away from where I live.  I want to work at a Kroger cause I know I can make almost four dollars an hour more then what I am making now.  

On another note it absolutely sucks living with an ex-boyfriend and his new wife.  Esp. when you don't have anyone at all.  I would like someone that I can date and cuddle and be with.  In time in time I need to keep saying to myself.
